{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_17","type":"agent_message","text":"I found the main hidden-risk area: the parser validates in one pass, so a function call can be marked undefined when the target function is declared later. I’m going to make global function discovery order-independent, keep local variables order-sensitive, and tighten incremental change handling while preserving the visible behavior."}}
